00:56:41,930 --> 00:56:44,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's rip 'em apart!

678
00:56:49,700 --> 00:56:51,840
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're not going to find it in here, Norman.

679
00:56:51,900 --> 00:56:53,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is useless!

680
00:56:53,300 --> 00:56:54,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah, I know, and it's also really boring.

681
00:56:55,040 --> 00:56:57,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I thought I was driving the van.

682
00:56:57,140 --> 00:57:00,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No one told me I was going to have to do this other dumb stuff.

683
00:57:01,210 --> 00:57:03,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If I had known there was so much reading involved,

684
00:57:03,450 --> 00:57:06,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I would have brought a completely different group of people who hate me.

685
00:57:06,180 --> 00:57:08,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes! Book number one, finished!

686
00:57:08,690 --> 00:57:12,260
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That is right. Twenty-six pages.

687
00:57:12,320 --> 00:57:13,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, yeah!

688
00:57:20,870 --> 00:57:22,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can't believe this is your plan.

689
00:57:22,770 --> 00:57:25,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to get bitten and start eating people's brains.

690
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:26,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm supposed to be vegan!

691
00:57:26,670 --> 00:57:29,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's something moving out there. I think it's the zombies.

692
00:57:29,210 --> 00:57:30,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hide!

693
00:57:30,380 --> 00:57:32,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, no, it's not. It's just grown-ups.

694
00:57:32,210 --> 00:57:33,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hide!

695
00:57:38,180 --> 00:57:40,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That sound. Do you know what that is?

696
00:57:40,690 --> 00:57:43,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's not awesome things.

697
00:57:43,190 --> 00:57:44,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Guys, come on!

698
00:57:44,490 --> 00:57:46,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just give it up, you wiener.

699
00:57:46,460 --> 00:57:47,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, we have to keep trying.

700
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:50,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Uh! We tried, and look what happened.

701
00:57:50,700 --> 00:57:54,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm scared, Norman, and I can't listen to this any more.

702
00:57:54,100 --> 00:57:56,840
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You never listen. No one ever listens!

703
00:57:57,140 --> 00:57:59,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm scared, too, but I've still got to do this.

704
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:01,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I do too listen!

705
00:58:01,110 --> 00:58:03,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And whatever it was you just said, it's not working.

706
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:06,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You think you're going to go out there, do your "talking to the dead" thing,

707
00:58:06,480 --> 00:58:09,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and this is all going to be okay?

708
00:58:09,150 --> 00:58:12,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you going to do? Huh? Ask the zombies not to eat you?

709
00:58:12,550 --> 00:58:14,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I should have known you wouldn't understand.

710
00:58:14,690 --> 00:58:16,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No one ever does!

711
00:58:16,120 --> 00:58:19,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman, you need to stop all this weird stuff,

712
00:58:19,690 --> 00:58:21,260
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and start living in the real world.

713
00:58:21,330 --> 00:58:23,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Everyone in the real world thinks I'm a freak!

714
00:58:23,660 --> 00:58:26,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you know what? Maybe they're right. Maybe I am a freak.

715
00:58:26,560 --> 00:58:29,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But I never asked for your help! Just go!

716
00:58:29,630 --> 00:58:31,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Get out!

717
00:58:31,640 --> 00:58:33,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Jeez, that was dramatic.

718
00:58:33,940 --> 00:58:35,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ugh! Come on!

719
00:58:44,820 --> 00:58:47,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not going anywhere. You can't make me.

720
00:58:49,750 --> 00:58:51,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Dude, you're really heavy.

721
00:58:51,190 --> 00:58:54,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not speaking to you. You can't make me.

722
00:59:03,230 --> 00:59:05,240
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Um, excuse me! Hello?

723
00:59:11,340 --> 00:59:15,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're in there, all right. I can feel its clammy flesh!

724
00:59:27,160 --> 00:59:28,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello?

725
00:59:43,270 --> 00:59:46,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Help! Somebody, help me!

726
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:48,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's burn them out!

727
00:59:53,150 --> 00:59:55,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're all going to die!

728
01:00:18,280 --> 01:00:20,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my gosh.

729
01:00:20,140 --> 01:00:22,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you think this has got anything to do with Norman?

730
01:00:22,750 --> 01:00:24,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course not.

731
01:00:24,120 --> 01:00:25,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Everyone, look!

732
01:00:27,090 --> 01:00:28,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Perry, do something!

733
01:00:29,420 --> 01:00:31,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman! Get down from there this instant!

734
01:00:31,920 --> 01:00:34,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're supposed to be grounded!

735
01:00:35,330 --> 01:00:38,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You horrible old witch! Is this what you want?

736
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:42,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Necromancer!

737
01:00:42,970 --> 01:00:44,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is all his doing!

738
01:00:44,170 --> 01:00:45,170
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman!

739
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:51,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Once upon a time, in a far-off land,

740
01:00:51,680 --> 01:00:55,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}there lived a king and a queen in a magnificent castle."

741
01:00:56,380 --> 01:00:59,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why won't you listen to me? Why are you doing this?

742
01:01:31,050 --> 01:01:36,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Agatha Prenderghast of His Majesty's province of Massachusetts,

743
01:01:37,160 --> 01:01:39,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}on this day you have been arraigned

744
01:01:39,720 --> 01:01:43,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}for the horrible crime of witchcraft

745
01:01:44,130 --> 01:01:49,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}witnessed by those whose testimonies have been heard.

746
01:01:49,970 --> 01:01:54,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have, by this court, been found guilty!

747
01:01:54,370 --> 01:01:55,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No!

748
01:01:55,610 --> 01:01:58,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And it is passed on you,

749
01:01:58,440 --> 01:02:01,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}according to your grievous crimes,

750
01:02:01,610 --> 01:02:03,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}execution!

751
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:11,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! No!

752
01:02:13,390 --> 01:02:17,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you have anything to say for yourself?

753
01:02:17,160 --> 01:02:18,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was only playing.

754
01:02:19,630 --> 01:02:21,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Aye! With fire!

755
01:02:21,300 --> 01:02:24,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You were speaking with the dead!

756
01:02:24,340 --> 01:02:29,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Wait! No!      - I'll not risk damnation on these good people.

757
01:02:29,310 --> 01:02:30,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, you can't do this!

758
01:02:30,940 --> 01:02:32,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't do anything wrong!

759
01:02:32,640 --> 01:02:33,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You are to be taken to the place of execution

760
01:02:33,750 --> 01:02:36,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}where you will be hanged by the neck

761
01:02:36,380 --> 01:02:37,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}until you be dead.

762
01:02:37,680 --> 01:02:38,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop!

763
01:02:39,020 --> 01:02:41,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave me alone or I'll make you sorry!

764
01:02:41,720 --> 01:02:44,170
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll make all of you sorry!

765
01:03:24,730 --> 01:03:27,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How could you?

766
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:29,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She was just a little kid.

767
01:03:30,330 --> 01:03:32,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She was no different than me.

768
01:03:35,140 --> 01:03:36,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep away from me!

769
01:03:38,080 --> 01:03:44,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You must stop the curse.

770
01:03:45,880 --> 01:03:47,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

771
01:03:48,290 --> 01:03:49,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You don't want to kill me?

772
01:03:50,520 --> 01:03:53,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can speak to the dead.

773
01:03:54,860 --> 01:03:56,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}To us.

774
01:03:57,260 --> 01:03:59,260
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}To her.

775
01:03:59,960 --> 01:04:04,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We need you to read from the book

776
01:04:04,270 --> 01:04:08,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to send us all back to the grave.

777
01:04:12,740 --> 01:04:14,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But it didn't work!

778
01:04:14,810 --> 01:04:16,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's a fairytale!

779
01:04:16,880 --> 01:04:19,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just a bedtime story.

780
01:04:22,220 --> 01:04:23,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's it, isn't it?

781
01:04:23,990 --> 01:04:27,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A bedtime story, to keep a little girl asleep for another year.

782
01:04:29,390 --> 01:04:31,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And now you need my help because

783
01:04:31,630 --> 01:04:34,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm the only one who can read it to her.

784
01:04:35,300 --> 01:04:37,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here's your book!

785
01:04:37,670 --> 01:04:39,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Try reading it yourself.

786
01:04:42,940 --> 01:04:44,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why did you do it?

787
01:04:46,110 --> 01:04:48,250
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We were scared.

788
01:04:48,910 --> 01:04:50,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of what?

789
01:04:51,120 --> 01:04:52,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of her.

790
01:04:55,490 --> 01:04:59,830
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I believed we were doing what was right.

791
01:05:01,590 --> 01:05:04,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was wrong.

792
01:05:04,860 --> 01:05:08,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, this is our punishment.

793
01:05:09,100 --> 01:05:12,270
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We thought we knew our way in life,

794
01:05:12,340 --> 01:05:14,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but in death,

795
01:05:14,970 --> 01:05:17,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}we are lost.

796
01:05:18,010 --> 01:05:21,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please help us.

797
01:05:23,550 --> 01:05:27,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Every year, someone reads the story at her grave.

798
01:05:28,150 --> 01:05:30,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Before me, it was Mr. Prenderghast,

799
01:05:30,920 --> 01:05:34,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and before him, there were others,

800
01:05:34,890 --> 01:05:37,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but the curse doesn't ever go away.

801
01:05:38,060 --> 01:05:42,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nothing gets better. It's not enough.

802
01:05:43,370 --> 01:05:45,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What will you do?

803
01:05:47,140 --> 01:05:50,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Something nobody ever did before.

804
01:05:51,680 --> 01:05:53,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've got to go talk to her.

805
01:06:00,690 --> 01:06:03,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Guys, guys! Under here, under here!

806
01:06:05,320 --> 01:06:08,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mitch, Mitch, if we die tonight,

807
01:06:08,760 --> 01:06:11,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}this may be the last chance I get to tell you how I feel.

808
01:06:11,800 --> 01:06:14,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Uh, well, no, unless we get brought back as zombies,

809
01:06:15,030 --> 01:06:17,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and then, technically, you'll have longer.

810
01:06:22,110 --> 01:06:23,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman?

811
01:06:23,740 --> 01:06:25,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on! This way!

812
01:06:25,910 --> 01:06:27,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You've got to be kidding me.

813
01:06:43,890 --> 01:06:45,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You stay right where you are!

814
01:06:46,100 --> 01:06:49,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You may be dead already, but I will still shoot you!

815
01:06:49,670 --> 01:06:51,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Wait!      - Oh, my gosh.

816
01:06:53,100 --> 01:06:56,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Son! Step away from the zombies!

817
01:06:56,410 --> 01:06:57,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, I won't.

818
01:06:58,080 --> 01:07:00,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Perry, calm down!

819
01:07:00,340 --> 01:07:02,800
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're going to have a heart attack, and then what are you going to do?

820
01:07:02,850 --> 01:07:04,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll come back and haunt Norman!

821
01:07:04,680 --> 01:07:06,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe then he'll start listening to me.

822
01:07:06,450 --> 01:07:09,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! No, you don't understand what's happening here.

823
01:07:09,550 --> 01:07:12,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I spoke to them, and it's not what you think.

824
01:07:12,520 --> 01:07:15,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The curse isn't about the zombies hurting you,

825
01:07:15,560 --> 01:07:17,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it's about you hurting them.

826
01:07:17,600 --> 01:07:20,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I figured it out, and I know a way to stop this.

827
01:07:20,800 --> 01:07:22,400
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's in league with them!

828
01:07:22,470 --> 01:07:24,140
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's hang him!

829
01:07:24,200 --> 01:07:26,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We can't hang him, stupid! It's the 21st century!

830
01:07:27,000 --> 01:07:28,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then let's burn him!

831
01:07:28,370 --> 01:07:31,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can you stop being a mob for just one minute?

832
01:07:31,780 --> 01:07:32,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Listen to me!

833
01:07:33,010 --> 01:07:35,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Get them before they eat us!

834
01:07:39,220 --> 01:07:40,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave him alone!

835
01:07:51,400 --> 01:07:54,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hand, Alvin. My hand.

836
01:07:56,930 --> 01:07:58,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Everybody, listen up!

837
01:07:58,970 --> 01:08:02,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You all need to stop trying to kill my brother!

838
01:08:02,570 --> 01:08:03,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're adults!

839
01:08:04,710 --> 01:08:05,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You stop it!

840
01:08:05,840 --> 01:08:08,120
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know that this seems crazy.

841
01:08:08,180 --> 01:08:10,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Believe me, lam with you on that.

842
01:08:10,350 --> 01:08:14,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But I think he does actually know what he's talking about.

843
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:18,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All night, he's been trying to save you from the witch's curse.

844
01:08:18,590 --> 01:08:20,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah! Yeah!

845
01:08:20,660 --> 01:08:25,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And all you want to do is burn and murder stuff, burn and murder stuff.

846
01:08:25,400 --> 01:08:27,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just burning and murdering.

847
01:08:27,570 --> 01:08:30,440
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah, shame on every single one of you!

848
01:08:30,500 --> 01:08:32,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How dare you all?

849
01:08:33,440 --> 01:08:36,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, they're not going to hurt us?

850
01:08:36,340 --> 01:08:37,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No.

851
01:08:37,880 --> 01:08:40,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Does it look like any of them are trying to hurt you?

852
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:42,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're just people.

853
01:08:43,110 --> 01:08:45,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, at least they used to be.

854
01:08:46,020 --> 01:08:48,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just stupid people who should have known better.

855
01:08:48,950 --> 01:08:53,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They did something unforgivable because they were scared,

856
01:08:53,790 --> 01:08:55,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and they were cursed for it.

857
01:08:55,930 --> 01:08:57,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now it's happening all over again.

858
01:08:58,800 --> 01:09:02,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you get it? They were just like you.

859
01:09:02,700 --> 01:09:04,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But now it has to stop.

860
01:09:05,040 --> 01:09:06,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For good.

861
01:09:45,240 --> 01:09:47,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Jeez, what is her problem?

862
01:09:54,050 --> 01:09:55,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, Norman!

863
01:09:57,820 --> 01:09:59,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, what do we do now?

864
01:10:00,020 --> 01:10:02,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I really don't know.

865
01:10:02,260 --> 01:10:03,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, you do, Norman.

866
01:10:03,660 --> 01:10:05,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You've got to get to that witch's grave.

867
01:10:05,600 --> 01:10:07,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- But...     - But nothing! Listen to me, buster.

868
01:10:07,630 --> 01:10:11,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We didn't turn away when Daleridge High was slaughtering our volleyball team, did we?

869
01:10:11,700 --> 01:10:13,240
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I thought we did.      - No, we didn't.

870
01:10:13,300 --> 01:10:16,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have cheered the uncheerable, Norman,

871
01:10:16,270 --> 01:10:18,750
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and I'm not letting you give up now!

872
01:10:20,610 --> 01:10:22,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Dad, could I borrow the car?

873
01:10:23,050 --> 01:10:24,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excuse me?

874
01:10:24,650 --> 01:10:26,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Officials are urging people to panic and run...

875
01:10:43,500 --> 01:10:47,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Whoo, boy. The traffic tonight, huh?

876
01:10:49,270 --> 01:10:51,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman! Uh!

877
01:10:51,410 --> 01:10:53,550
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's on my side of the seat.

878
01:10:53,910 --> 01:10:55,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She wants you to move over.

879
01:10:57,720 --> 01:10:59,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Um, I heard that!

880
01:10:59,620 --> 01:11:01,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mom, tell the zombie to stop saying stuff about me.

881
01:11:01,690 --> 01:11:04,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can you quit using the "Z" word?

882
01:11:04,290 --> 01:11:06,460
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So help me, I will stop this car right now

883
01:11:06,520 --> 01:11:09,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}if all three of you don't quit it this instant!

884
01:11:16,370 --> 01:11:19,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He says, take a left here.

885
01:11:19,240 --> 01:11:22,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We've already been this way! We're going around in circles!

886
01:11:22,570 --> 01:11:24,880
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe we should pull over and ask someone.

887
01:11:24,940 --> 01:11:27,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, right! You think maybe we should stop at a graveyard

888
01:11:27,910 --> 01:11:30,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and dig up some other 18th-century corpses?

889
01:11:30,780 --> 01:11:32,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's not a bad idea.

890
01:11:33,120 --> 01:11:35,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I wish I understood you.

891
01:11:38,190 --> 01:11:40,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please don't tell me he needs to use the bathroom.

892
01:11:40,720 --> 01:11:42,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Turn down there!

893
01:11:46,200 --> 01:11:50,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my. Do you think that's it?

894
01:11:55,170 --> 01:11:58,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, why are we here?

895
01:12:00,340 --> 01:12:02,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Someone has got to talk to her, Dad.

896
01:12:03,050 --> 01:12:07,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. Why is that person you, exactly?

897
01:12:21,900 --> 01:12:24,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my goodness. Look out!

898
01:12:24,570 --> 01:12:25,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mom!

899
01:12:25,870 --> 01:12:27,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Perry! Do something!

900
01:12:27,400 --> 01:12:29,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I am trying!

901
01:12:29,170 --> 01:12:30,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kick it in the knothole!

902
01:12:33,840 --> 01:12:35,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Norman?

903
01:12:37,010 --> 01:12:39,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm okay, Mom!

904
01:12:39,650 --> 01:12:41,890
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just wait for me here. Don't worry.

905
01:12:41,950 --> 01:12:43,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Be careful!

906
01:13:19,790 --> 01:13:21,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello?

907
01:13:22,360 --> 01:13:24,170
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not welcome here.

908
01:13:24,560 --> 01:13:26,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Go away.

909
01:13:28,870 --> 01:13:31,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I really need to speak with you.

910
01:13:31,640 --> 01:13:33,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who are you?

911
01:13:33,800 --> 01:13:37,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm Norman. Norman Babcock.

912
01:13:37,070 --> 01:13:41,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You don't actually know me, but I know you.

913
01:13:41,650 --> 01:13:44,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're actually kind of the same, you and I.

914
01:13:44,350 --> 01:13:45,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not dead.

915
01:13:46,380 --> 01:13:49,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, no, apart from that.

916
01:13:49,220 --> 01:13:51,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you're a boy.

917
01:13:51,490 --> 01:13:53,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, yes. That, too.

918
01:13:54,260 --> 01:13:56,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not like me at all!

919
01:13:57,330 --> 01:13:59,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, I know how you feel.

920
01:13:59,760 --> 01:14:03,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, you don't. You don't know anything about me.

921
01:14:03,630 --> 01:14:05,840
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know your name is Agatha Prenderghast.

922
01:14:05,900 --> 01:14:06,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

923
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:10,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I know you're probably tired, right?

924
01:14:10,110 --> 01:14:12,710
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because, I mean, it's really late,

925
01:14:12,780 --> 01:14:15,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and it's been a long night,

926
01:14:15,450 --> 01:14:18,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and we're, like, only 11 years old, and...

927
01:14:18,680 --> 01:14:22,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't want to go to sleep, and you can't make me.

928
01:14:58,390 --> 01:15:00,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I burned the book into dust.

929
01:15:01,160 --> 01:15:04,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now I don't have to listen to that stupid story any more!

930
01:15:12,140 --> 01:15:14,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave me alone.

931
01:15:16,970 --> 01:15:19,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. No, I'm not leaving.

932
01:15:19,540 --> 01:15:21,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just listen to me.

933
01:15:22,480 --> 01:15:24,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Once upon a time,

934
01:15:24,280 --> 01:15:27,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}long ago, there was a little girl.

935
01:15:27,450 --> 01:15:28,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

936
01:15:28,550 --> 01:15:31,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A little girl who was different...

937
01:15:31,660 --> 01:15:34,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who was different from the other people in her village.

